                                                                                                                                Buttons

                                                                                                                                Button

                                                                                                                                Stable

                                                                                                                                Buttons are controls that let users take action, make choices, and move forward.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Content
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog

                                                                                                                                Button label style

                                                                                                                                Button labels indicate what happens when the user taps the button, distilling the action a user wants to take into a few words.

                                                                                                                                Do

                                                                                                                                Use 1-3 words max on one line (a few words in English may be an entire phrase in another language)

                                                                                                                                Use sentence case

                                                                                                                                Make button labels work with the header. Users should be able to scan only the header and button labels to understand precisely what they can do

                                                                                                                                Use one action per button. Think you need two actions on one button? It's likely a sign that you need to add a step in the flow or alter the design

                                                                                                                                Use articles (a, an, the), the space allowing. ESL users have difficulty understanding text with no articles

                                                                                                                                Don't

                                                                                                                                No symbols, like +


                                                                                                                                No variable, like numbers


                                                                                                                                No periods, commas, exclamation points

                                                                                                                                No pronouns (I, me, and us)



                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Use 1 – 3 words. For longer strings, place the text outside the button.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use wordy labels that wrap lines. *The only exception can be for dynamic type resizing.
                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Use sentence case, always.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use all uppercase letters. They are harder to read, and there’s no need to shout.

                                                                                                                                Primary buttons

                                                                                                                                Content in primary buttons helps users take a specific action, move forward in a flow, acknowledge & dismiss, or finish a task.

                                                                                                                                Follow these guidelines for labeling:

                                                                                                                                Do use simple imperatives (action verb + object) to indicate what happens when the button is tapped

                                                                                                                                Do capture the user's highest-level intent at this moment, even if there are subsequent steps

                                                                                                                                Don't add "now" to a label. It's implied that the action will occur after the user taps

                                                                                                                                Primary button type


                                                                                                                                Use


                                                                                                                                Avoid

                                                                                                                                Take a specific action

                                                                                                                                Request UberX

                                                                                                                                Request UberX now (now is implied)


                                                                                                                                Reserve bike


                                                                                                                                Get started (sounds like a long process)


                                                                                                                                Try again


                                                                                                                                Retry


                                                                                                                                Confirm price




                                                                                                                                Send report




                                                                                                                                Verify payment



                                                                                                                                Moving forward in low

                                                                                                                                Next

                                                                                                                                Continue

                                                                                                                                Acknowledge & dismiss

                                                                                                                                OK

                                                                                                                                Okay


                                                                                                                                Got it

                                                                                                                                Got it! (no exclamation point)


                                                                                                                                I agree (for "official" consent scenarios, e.g. community guidelines)

                                                                                                                                Yes

                                                                                                                                Finish a task

                                                                                                                                Got it




                                                                                                                                Save




                                                                                                                                Confirm (when the title in header already makes it clear what task the user is completing)



                                                                                                                                Secondary buttons

                                                                                                                                Secondary buttons can often appear in line with list items and other elements, letting users modify something. In these cases, don’t include a noun just to reiterate what the user is taking action on—secondary buttons should speak for themselves in the context of the UI.


                                                                                                                                Use


                                                                                                                                Avoid

                                                                                                                                Edit

                                                                                                                                Edit address

                                                                                                                                (Don’t include nouns when a button is in close proximity to the object)

                                                                                                                                Change

                                                                                                                                Change destination

                                                                                                                                (Don’t include nouns when a button is in close proximity to the object)

                                                                                                                                Tertiary Buttons

                                                                                                                                Tertiary buttons are mainly used for dismissive actions that give users a way out of something, letting them do nothing, dismiss, or skip.

                                                                                                                                When possible, use a more precise verb that captures the inverse of the primary action (e.g., Cancel reservation / Keep reservation) .

                                                                                                                                See also, Opposite Actions below.



                                                                                                                                Use


                                                                                                                                Avoid

                                                                                                                                Not now (decline an action for later)

                                                                                                                                Maybe later (too noncommittal)

                                                                                                                                No thanks (decline an action permanently)

                                                                                                                                Later

                                                                                                                                Skip

                                                                                                                                Decline

                                                                                                                                Go back



                                                                                                                                Related actions

                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Two or more buttons that offer different ways to do the same thing or different actions that have a clear relationship. The primary button should be the main action; the secondary button can offer alternatives to that action.


                                                                                                                                When you have two or more different actions on your buttons, include nouns after each verb to be clear what the action applies to.


                                                                                                                                Don’t introduce new words or concepts. This is especially important when offering related but distinct choices to users.

                                                                                                                                Opposite actions

                                                                                                                                Opposite actions are two buttons that have an opposite or inverse relationship. The primary button is the main, sometimes destructive action, and a tertiary button typically undoes or offers a way out of that action.


                                                                                                                                Do


                                                                                                                                Don't

                                                                                                                                Try to use verbs with the opposite meaning to signal to the user what happens when they tap. (E.g. Cancel order | Continue order)

                                                                                                                                Don't use Yes and No as labels

                                                                                                                                Make button labels work with the header. Users should be able to scan the header and button labels to understand what they can do

                                                                                                                                When the task at hand is canceling something, don't use cancel as the dismissive action label (E.g. Cancel trip | Cancel)



                                                                                                                                Don't introduce a new concept or word in the primary button that isn't in the header or immediately clear in the user's context


                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Do use verbs with the opposite meaning and indicate what happens after users tap.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use Yes and No as labels.
                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Do use verbs that have the opposite meaning to signal to the user what happens when they tap.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t use cancel as the dismissive action when the task is cancelling itself.


                                                                                                                                Content for circle buttons


                                                                                                                                Circular buttons should be used only with a single icon inside or with text that is never longer than two characters, such as initials or numbers from 1 to 9.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Circular buttons work well with one element inside, or a maximum of two initials. These guidelines work well in any language.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don’t include words or currency, even if they are short in English. They will break in other languages and countries (e.g., MXN$290). Use the pill button for these cases instead.
